You can copy code from the [GOV.UK Design System](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/) to add page elements like radio buttons and text inputs.

## Add radios to question 1

1. Go to the [stacked radios section of the Design System](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/radios/#stacked-radios).
2. Click **HTML** and copy the example HTML code.
3. Open `juggling-balls.html` in your `app/views` folder.
4. Replace the 2 example `<p>...</p>` paragraphs with the example HTML code you copied.
5. In your copied code, replace the text in the `<h1>` tags with the page's title text: `How many balls can you juggle?`.

Replace the text in the 3 `<label>` tags with:

- `3 or more`
- `1 or 2`
- `None - I cannot juggle`

Replace the 3 `value` parameters with:

- `value="3 or more"`
- `value="1 or 2"`
- `value="None - I cannot juggle"`

Replace all 3 `name="where-do-you-live"` parameters with `name="number-of-balls"`.

